    "created_at": "2015-04-07T10:20:21Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-04-07T10:20:21Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "If you want to display values as ratio of column/row/table total like Excel/Calc allows, here's a piece of code which will do the job:\n\n```\nif display_value == \"col_ratio\":\n    # Display values as a ratio of column total\n    table = table.div(table.sum(axis=0), axis=1)\nelif display_value == \"row_ratio\":\n    # Display values as a ratio of row total\n    table = table.div(table.sum(axis=1), axis=0)\nelif display_value == \"total_ratio\":\n    # Display values as a ratio of table total\n    table = table.div(table.sum().sum())\n```\n"
  },
